            behind the protocol. It licenses technology, operates an optional
            frontend, and provides KYC rails. It does not operate the protocol,
            custody metal, or issue CCTs. Client-facing CCT fees are legally vault
            fees: the vault issues the CCT and pays the OpCo's technology-service
            slice. Protocol-economic fees flow to the Foundation Treasury. Every
            revenue line is recipient-tagged in the financial model:
          </p>
