        <!-- 7 · GOLD POSITION -->
        <section id="gold-position" class="memo-section" data-memo-section>
          <h2 class="display display--md">V. The $2 Million Productive Gold-Liquidity Treasury</h2>
          <p>
            Forty percent of the Seed launches the first Global Gold markets.
            At platform activation, the Company deploys $2M across six gold/gold
            pools: USG/PAXG, USG/XAUT, XAUT/PAXG, gGold/USG, gGold/PAXG, and
            gGold/XAUT. This gives the network immediate tradability and creates
            the market depth required for users, vaults, arbitrageurs, and
            integrations to transact from day one.
          </p>
          <p>
            The position remains productive while it performs that role. It earns
            pool trading fees, recycles those fees back into liquidity, and
            remains denominated entirely in gold-referenced assets. If gold
            appreciates, the treasury position appreciates with it while
            continuing to deepen the network's markets. In the active Base case,
            the $2M position grows to approximately $5.1M by Year 5 through modeled
            gold appreciation and reinvested fees.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Base model assumes external liquidity reaches approximately 50%
            of the OpCo position by Year 1 and 500% by Year 5. The Treasury Policy
            keeps the position focused on market quality, productive deployment,
            and disciplined rebalancing as the ecosystem matures.
          </p>
