        <!-- 9 · MOAT -->
        <section id="moat" class="memo-section" data-memo-section>
          <h2 class="display display--md">VII. The Moat</h2>
          <p>Three legs. Each alone is replicable. Together, they are not.</p>
          <ol class="memo-list memo-list--numbered">
            <li>
              <strong>Distribution and Workflow.</strong> The free Title Register
              becomes part of a vault's records, KYC, settlement, and audit
              workflow. Each binding integration makes the network more useful and
              raises operational switching costs.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Neutral Coordination.</strong> Single issuers and regional
              hubs can build technology, but a neutral multi-vault standard asks
              them to agree on governance, admissions, liability, data, fee
              allocation, and control—often against existing economics.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Regulatory-Defensibility Engineering.</strong> Patent
              filings document deliberate implementation choices and preserve
              potential exclusion or licensing rights within a broader moat of
              distribution, liquidity, governance, integrations, and operating
              history.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>

