              for the U.S. Blockchain Coalition, and previously led negotiations
              around an $11.5M renewable-energy financing and subsequent $16M
              sale.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            <strong>Governance.</strong> Global Gold is built around a
            deliberately separated three-pillar structure: the operating company
            builds and commercializes the technology; the Global Gold Council, a
            Wyoming DUNA under Wyo. Stat. § 17-32, sets and maintains the protocol
            standards; and a neutral Foundation, structured as a Swiss charitable
            Stiftung, serves as the ecosystem's permanent steward.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Foundation holds the single ecosystem treasury, applies the
            Council's standards to counterparty admissions, and stewards the
            protocol IP through a neutral head-license structure, while operating
            no protocol and taking custody of no metal. The OpCo board at Seed
            will have three seats: one designated by each Founder and one by the
            lead investor. Founder-held super-voting common stock will carry
            20 votes per share, subject to customary transfer,
            service, ownership, and public-company sunset terms. The Series Seed
            receives customary protective provisions over major corporate actions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 12 · THE ROUND -->
        <section id="round" class="memo-section" data-memo-section>
          <h2 class="display display--md">XI. The Round</h2>
          <p>
            $5M priced Series Seed at $50M post: 1x non-participating preference,
            a 10% option pool from pre-money, a three-person Board with one
            lead-investor seat, founder-held super-voting common stock carrying
            20 votes per share, customary preferred protective provisions, and a
            segregated Treasury Policy for the $2M market-capital allocation.
            Standard NVCA definitive documents, drafted by Babb Reed &amp; Leak LLP
            with Paul Hastings LLP advising on relevant regulatory architecture.
            The round may be completed in one or more closings on identical terms;
            minimum check $100k. The data room includes the
            financial model (live workbook), the term sheet, the research census,
            the patent filings, the DUNA formation package, and the Wyoming
            Reserve partnership documentation.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>The One-Paragraph Case.</strong> Demand for on-chain gold is
            proven by billions of dollars in single-issuer products. Supply is
            stranded in 40–80 vaults with no pathway. Global Gold connects the two
            with the only architecture in which the vault keeps title, no company
            owns the market, and every fee is earned against real metal —
            through a separated architecture and a bottom-up demand-and-supply
            engine. The core MVP is live on testnet; the Wyoming Reserve has
            signed an MOU; Texas is in active discussions; and Global Gold has
            built a 10,000+ member gold-and-DeFi community. The Seed takes the
            system through Tier 1 audit, activates the first vault and liquidity
            markets, and turns a working protocol into the first operating network
            for global allocated-gold settlement.
          </p>

